lead_paragraph: An article in some copies last Sunday about Texas Tech’s victory over Oklahoma State in college football that kept its national title hopes alive referred incorrectly to the skyline of the “West Texas outpost” of Lubbock. It does indeed have buildings taller than 14 stories — at least two.
